WHAT IS SEMANTIC ELEMENT  ?  

Semantic or Semantics relates to meaning in language.it is defined as more meaningful.. Semantic HTML is simply markup that is more effective at communicating some intended meaning. 

1)Clearer code and easier to maintain  

2) Help your site be accessible  

3) Improve your SEO positioning 

4)Semantic HTML Conveys More relative  Meaning  


  				                                                            Semantic Elements 


<header>  -->  <header> to be used for a web page header which typically contains the site logo, heading elements, and site navigation. 

 -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

<footer>  --> to be used for a web page footer which typically contains authorship, contact, copyright information, in addition to navigational links and a link back to the top of the web page. 

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

<main>  --> <main> used to contain all of the content inside of main wrapper. the main element should be used at most once on a single page.

     
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

<nav> -->  An element to contain blocks of site navigation links. This element is typically placed in the page header and footer, and may also be used in an aside (sidebar) element as well. 

 -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

<section> -->  The section element is used to the section of the document is defined.

 -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 
<aside>  --> Use to identify content that is related to the main content on the page but not part of the primary flow of the document.
For example, the aside element may contain a glossary definition, new blog post, new features, advertisements that should be related to the contents of the page. 
 -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

<article>  --> The article element should be like blog post or technical article.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

<figure-> -->Specifies self-contained content, like that illustrations, diagrams, photos, code listings, etc. 
`<figcaption>`  --> Defines a caption for a <figure> element 

 -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 
<Details and Summary>-->  details is a wrapper for  a summary element.<details> is contains more additional information of summary element  but that begins collapsed. when you user By clicking on <details> to expand the summary, we reveal a long explanation.

  
 -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 
HTML header tags, more commonly known as <h1>, <h2>, <h3>, <h4>, <h5>, and <h6> tags, make it easier for people and search engines alike to get a quick understanding of what a page is about

The HTML <h1>–<h6> elements represent six levels of section headings. it's hierarchical system of headline. that provide search engine convey the meaning  which is most important versus which is less important tell the browser and then  <h1> should be used at once one time. don't use repeating.if you want use <h1> element in multiple places.there are no problem. but whatever are you typing <h1> if you use different places if give relative before typed

<p> ---> it's used for paragraph often 

 -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

<i>  and  <em> same visual displaying but there are not the same semantic meaning human meaning different result. 

<i> visual only italics  

<em> emphasis italics (stress make the text) 

 --------------------------------------------
<b> and <strong> these are the same visual displayed, but user hearing to use accessibility. it's the different result of the sound
 
 -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

<strong>  --> Hi, browser i am strong tag convey the browser importance seriousness, urgency. 

use h2,h3,h4 instead of don't use more this tag 
 -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

<kbd> , <samp> , <code> are same visual effect but semantic different element using its default monospace font 

<kbd> --> Text that indicates user input from a keyboard, voice input, or any other text entry device. 

 <code> --> Text that indicates a short fragment of a computer code. 

 <samp> --> represents sample computer output, and originally computers were monospaced :) 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

 
                              Non Semantic Elements 
                               
<div> and then span These tags don’t tell the computer anything about the meaning of the contents of the element. 

 

 
